hy_it_can_fail":"A single composite can mask a weak component; open the Fundamentals tab for the breakdown."},{"label":"Cash conversion","value":0.63,"unit":"\u00d7","status":"ok","read":"0.63\u00d7 \u2014 partly cash-backed.","meaning":"Median of (cash from operations \u00f7 net profit) over the last 5 years.","why_useful":"Profit you can't collect as cash is fragile; >0.8\u00d7 means earnings are real cash, <0.6\u00d7 is an accrual red flag.","why_it_can_fail":"One-off working-capital swings or a capex year can distort a single ratio; the 5-yr median smooths it."},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":0.03,"unit":"\u00d7 D/E","status":"good","read":"Conservatively financed (D/E 0.03\u00d7, interest cover 11.7\u00d7).","meaning":"Latest debt-to-equity and interest coverage (EBIT \u00f7 interest) from the balance sheet.","why_useful":"Low debt and high interest cover let a business survive a downturn; high debt amplifies trouble.","why_it_can_fail":"Off-balance-sheet leases/guarantees aren't captured; a cash-rich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":-32.37,"unit":"% YoY","status":"weak","read":"Profit down 32% YoY (latest TTM).","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":21.1,"pe_percentile":51.0,"median_pe":21.4,"earnings_yield_pct":4.74,"pb":1.97,"ev_ebitda":35.04,"quality_score":27.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":44.9,"peg":0.47,"cheapness":{"status":"ok","read":"P/E at the 51-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 mid-range vs its own history."},"expectations":"At 21.1\u00d7 earnings for ~45% 5-yr profit CAGR, the market is paying \u22480.47\u00d7 growth (PEG). >2 = a lot already priced in; <1 = cheap if growth holds.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"Promoter":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[67.12,67.15,67.19,67.31,67.31,67.18,66.62,66.65,65.1,62.29,62.43,62.46],"latest_pct":62.46,"chg_1y_pp":-4.19},"FII":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[2.39,3.72,3.5,3.55,3.57,3.71,4.56,3.81,4.28,5.21,3.92,3.8],"latest_pct":3.8,"chg_1y_pp":-0.01},"DII":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[1.67,2.1,2.09,2.1,2.09,1.69,2.15,2.16,2.12,2.03,2.03,1.93],"latest_pct":1.93,"chg_1y_pp":-0.23},"Public":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[28.81,27.02,27.19,27.04,27.04,27.4,26.66,27.37,28.49,30.47,31.61,31.79],"latest_pct":31.79,"chg_1y_pp":4.42}},"pledge":null,"events":[{"date":"15-Feb-2024","subject":"Interim Dividend - Rs 0.54 Per Share","materiality":"Low"},{"date":"30-Jul-2024","subject":"Annual General Meeting","materiality":"Med"},{"date":"19-Aug-2024